The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Md. Sporting fine players
                                                                                                                                                                                                     Md. Sporting fine players
            A STAFF REPORTER                      
	Calcutta: Mohammedan Sporting fined their foreign recruits Mike Okoro and Adewusi Adebayo on Friday for assaulting a journalist earlier this month.         
	At a meeting held on Friday evening, top officials of the club slapped a Rs 25,000 fine on Okoro. Adebayo was fined Rs 15,000. Both of them have been asked to offer an unconditional apology to the journalist for their behaviour.         
	The duo had assaulted a TV journalist at the teams practice at the Ravindra Sarobar Stadium during the recently-concluded Federation Cup.         
	Meanwhile, the meeting between the Indian Football Association (IFA) and Mohun Bagan on the IFA Shield bore no fruit on Friday. IFA and Bagan officials have decided to meet again on Tuesday.         
	We told them that since were the parent body, Bagan have to play in our tournament. They said that they will try their best, IFA secretary Utpal Ganguly said.         
	Anjan Mitra, the Bagan secretary, said: Weve reiterated that our players are very tired and as the parent body, IFA should understand our situation.                                                                                                                          
